01:37:10,722 --> 01:37:13,557
- I'll make an exception for you.
- Frank, you're a good cop.

1190
01:37:13,690 --> 01:37:16,784
<i>Stop being a prima donna.
Cut out the shticklech.</i>

1191
01:37:16,860 --> 01:37:18,987
I don't understand.

1192
01:37:19,062 --> 01:37:21,030
How am I being a prima donna?
I want to protect myself.

1193
01:37:23,500 --> 01:37:27,197
We're gonna get the indictments.
You're gonna have to testify.

1194
01:37:35,278 --> 01:37:39,146
<i>Ready on the right.
Ready on the left.</i>

1195
01:37:39,215 --> 01:37:42,048
<i>Ready on the firing line.</i>

1196
01:38:31,201 --> 01:38:33,635
What are you gonna tell
the grand jury, Frankie?

1197
01:38:35,872 --> 01:38:37,965
Depends on
what they ask me.

1198
01:38:38,041 --> 01:38:40,532
Suppose they ask you
who's taking money?

1199
01:38:40,610 --> 01:38:42,874
What I don't know,
I don't know.

1200
01:38:42,946 --> 01:38:45,676
But you do know, Frank.

1201
01:38:45,749 --> 01:38:49,742
Look, Frankie, I like you. I don't
want to see anything happen to you.

1202
01:38:49,819 --> 01:38:54,153
But you gotta understand,
a lot of people could get hurt here.

1203
01:38:54,224 --> 01:38:57,785
I'm not saying anything's going to
happen. I'm saying it could happen.

1204
01:38:57,861 --> 01:39:00,659
I mean, there's lots of ways.
Nobody has to take a shot at you.

1205
01:39:00,730 --> 01:39:02,891
They can just not be there
when you need them.

1206
01:39:02,966 --> 01:39:06,197
Somebody come at you with a gun,
they look the other way.

1207
01:39:06,269 --> 01:39:08,362
Or they can send you
in first enough times...

1208
01:39:08,438 --> 01:39:10,633
until finally one day you're gonna
walk in the wrong door.

1209
01:39:14,778 --> 01:39:17,144
- Thanks for the information.
- Fuck you, Frank!

1210
01:39:20,450 --> 01:39:23,044
I have nothing more. Does anyone
have any further questions?

1211
01:39:24,120 --> 01:39:26,384
- Yes, Mrs. Crist?
- If I may, Mr. Knowles, thank you.

1212
01:39:26,456 --> 01:39:29,118
Officer Serpico came
to the 7th Division...

1213
01:39:29,192 --> 01:39:31,126
more than a year
and a half ago.

1214
01:39:31,194 --> 01:39:34,561
All during that time, the things
he's told us were taking place.

1215
01:39:34,631 --> 01:39:37,293
Now, why didn't
Officer Serpico...

1216
01:39:37,367 --> 01:39:41,428
report these criminal activities
when he first encountered them?

1217
01:39:41,504 --> 01:39:44,667
- I'd like to answer that.
- Mr. Chairman...

1218
01:39:44,741 --> 01:39:49,474
Mrs. Crist's question isn't material
or relevant to the present inquiry.

1219
01:39:49,546 --> 01:39:51,776
- Although I want to make it clear...
- I'd like to answer that.

1220
01:39:51,848 --> 01:39:55,443
Officer Serpico cannot be considered
derelict of his duty in any way...

1221
01:39:55,518 --> 01:39:57,816
or guilty of
any infraction of the law.

1222
01:39:57,887 --> 01:39:59,821
Quite the contrary.

1223
01:39:59,889 --> 01:40:03,416
The District Attorney is not prepared
to say any more at this time.

1224
01:40:03,493 --> 01:40:06,929
Very well. Officer Serpico,
thank you for your testimony.

1225
01:40:06,996 --> 01:40:09,988
This hearing is adjourned
until 10:00 tomorrow morning.

1226
01:40:11,568 --> 01:40:14,560
Why didn't you tell him
about Delaney and Kellogg?

1227
01:40:14,637 --> 01:40:17,435
Frank, this was a grand jury
about police officers...

1228
01:40:17,507 --> 01:40:20,169
actively engaged in corruption.

1229
01:40:20,243 --> 01:40:22,905
You don't implicate people
without sufficient evidence.

1230
01:40:22,979 --> 01:40:26,915
That's crap and you know it, because
even a dumb cop like me knows...

1231
01:40:26,983 --> 01:40:30,578
a prosecutor can take a grand jury
anywhere it wants to take it.

1232
01:40:30,653 --> 01:40:33,349
Now, you never led me anywhere
near the real problems...

1233
01:40:33,423 --> 01:40:36,688
Nothing about the bosses,
the brass...

1234
01:40:36,760 --> 01:40:39,627
how corruption like this could exist
without anybody knowing about it.

1235
01:40:39,696 --> 01:40:42,290
Now, a few flunky cops
in the Bronx. That's it.

1236
01:40:42,365 --> 01:40:45,061
None of the shit in Queens,
Brooklyn, Manhattan?

1237
01:40:45,135 --> 01:40:47,035
While you're at it,
why don't you mention Kansas City?

1238
01:40:47,103 --> 01:40:49,503
Well, "the biggest thing since
Harry Gross." That's what you said.

1239
01:40:49,572 --> 01:40:52,006
All right! Look, Frank.

1240
01:40:52,876 --> 01:40:55,845
You got guts, integrity.

1241
01:40:55,912 --> 01:40:58,904
There's going to be a detective's
gold shield in this for you.

1242
01:41:01,584 --> 01:41:05,076
Now, that's terrific.
That's good.

1243
01:41:05,155 --> 01:41:06,747
Maybe this is
what it's all about.

1244
01:41:06,823 --> 01:41:08,688
Maybe I should take my
gold shield and forget it.

1245
01:41:08,758 --> 01:41:11,056
I know you've been through
an ordeal, Frank.

1246
01:41:13,830 --> 01:41:17,322
I'm a marked man in this department.
For what?

1247
01:41:17,400 --> 01:41:20,733
- I've already arranged a transfer.
- To where? China?

1248
01:41:32,682 --> 01:41:35,446
That takes a 14-shot clip.

1249
01:41:35,518 --> 01:41:37,543
You expecting an army?

1250
01:41:37,620 --> 01:41:39,554
No, just a division.

1251
01:41:41,491 --> 01:41:46,019
Tauber, did you know I've had
reports about Serpico being a fag?

1252
01:41:46,095 --> 01:41:48,791
He used to hang out
in the BCI washroom.

1253
01:41:48,865 --> 01:41:52,062
That's stupid, Commissioner,
and you know it.

1254
01:41:52,135 --> 01:41:56,231
Mr. Commissioner, a gold shield
for Serpico at this time...

1255
01:41:56,306 --> 01:41:57,933
would convince
a lot of people...

1256
01:41:58,007 --> 01:41:59,531
Not while I'm commissioner.

1257
01:42:18,761 --> 01:42:20,194
Commander's office?

1258
01:42:22,665 --> 01:42:24,599
It's down that corridor.

1259
01:42:27,570 --> 01:42:30,334
Hey, Serpico. Do you know what
they're saying in the Bronx?

1260
01:42:30,406 --> 01:42:33,273
That you spilled your
guts to the grand jury.

1261
01:42:34,277 --> 01:42:36,245
Say it isn't so, Serpico.

1262
01:42:38,414 --> 01:42:40,109
It isn't so.

1263
01:42:41,184 --> 01:42:43,277
We know how to handle
guys like you.

1264
01:42:44,520 --> 01:42:46,488
I ought to cut
your tongue out.

1265
01:42:52,328 --> 01:42:54,023
Don't move.

1266
01:43:16,119 --> 01:43:18,383
Officer Serpico
reporting for duty, sir.

1267
01:43:26,663 --> 01:43:29,632
I'm Inspector Lombardo.
I want to shake your hand, Frank.

1268
01:43:31,434 --> 01:43:33,664
It's gonna be nice to have
a guy here I can trust.

1269
01:43:35,405 --> 01:43:36,838
Anybody in this command
you want to work with?

1270
01:43:40,443 --> 01:43:44,174
It's not who I want to work with.
It's who wants to work with me.

1271
01:43:47,016 --> 01:43:50,577
All right. You can't find anybody
you want to work with, Frank...

1272
01:43:50,653 --> 01:43:52,883
I'll work with you.

1273
01:43:52,956 --> 01:43:54,890
Is that all right?

1274
01:44:05,601 --> 01:44:07,592
How do we get past
the lookouts?

1275
01:44:07,670 --> 01:44:09,399
How many you got?
One.

1276
01:44:11,941 --> 01:44:13,143
There's two.

1277
01:44:13,143 --> 01:44:14,508
There's two.

1278
01:44:14,577 --> 01:44:17,375
- Yeah, there's a guy.
- There's three of them.

1279
01:44:17,447 --> 01:44:19,642
It's four buildings away. We could
try to get down the fire escape.

1280
01:44:19,716 --> 01:44:21,809
Get in behind him.
What do you think?

1281
01:44:23,419 --> 01:44:25,751
- Look good to you?
- Yeah, let's go.

1282
01:45:08,798 --> 01:45:10,891
What do you think?
Want to try it?

1283
01:45:29,385 --> 01:45:31,615
- Oh, boy.
- You all right?

1284
01:45:31,688 --> 01:45:33,622
Yeah. I feel just
like a cop again.

1285
01:45:33,690 --> 01:45:35,954
- Let's go.
- Thank you.

1286
01:46:04,387 --> 01:46:05,945
Close up!

1287
01:46:08,791 --> 01:46:10,816
Wait, Frank!

1288
01:46:10,893 --> 01:46:12,326
Come on!

1289
01:46:21,771 --> 01:46:23,204
I ain't got nothing!

1290
01:46:25,408 --> 01:46:27,342
Beat it, fuck face!

1291
01:46:28,544 --> 01:46:31,980
Get the other one! Get out of here!
Get up against the wall.

1292
01:46:35,885 --> 01:46:38,149
What the hell's goin' on here?
Who the hell are you?

1293
01:46:38,221 --> 01:46:40,052
- Who are you?
- The police! Who the hell you think?

1294
01:46:40,123 --> 01:46:42,751
Get the fuck against the wall.
Up, up, up!

1295
01:46:42,825 --> 01:46:46,488
- Let me see your shield.
- All right. There's my shield.

1296
01:46:46,562 --> 01:46:49,224
- Where are you from?
- The borough. Manhattan 8th.

1297
01:46:49,299 --> 01:46:52,427
No, goddamn it! I just paid
the borough this morning!

1298
01:46:55,004 --> 01:46:56,699
What the hell kind of
shakedown is this?

1299
01:46:56,773 --> 01:46:58,866
Who'd you pay
in the borough?

1300
01:47:00,543 --> 01:47:03,011
Nobody.
I didn't pay no...

1301
01:47:03,079 --> 01:47:05,172
Who'd you pay
in the borough?

1302
01:47:05,248 --> 01:47:08,411
I didn't pay nobody.
Now let go of me.

1303
01:47:09,452 --> 01:47:14,048
We followed up,
and there's no doubt about it.

1304
01:47:14,123 --> 01:47:17,524
The pad here in Manhattan
is bigger...

1305
01:47:17,593 --> 01:47:22,326
and it's more sophisticated
than the one in the Bronx.

1306
01:47:22,398 --> 01:47:25,424
The pickups here are made...
You want to get this...

1307
01:47:25,501 --> 01:47:28,732
The pickups are made by...

1308
01:47:28,805 --> 01:47:31,672
retired policemen.

1309
01:47:31,741 --> 01:47:35,233
That way, no plainclothesmen
are directly involved.

1310
01:47:35,311 --> 01:47:39,543
Now, we need investigative help
on this one, Chief.

1311
01:47:41,384 --> 01:47:45,787
If you need investigative help
and you don't trust your own men...

1312
01:47:45,855 --> 01:47:48,881
why don't you requisition some
recruits from the police academy?

1313
01:47:57,166 --> 01:47:58,758
With all due respect,
sir...

1314
01:48:00,803 --> 01:48:03,704
backing us up is the only hope
the police department has got.

1315
01:48:03,773 --> 01:48:07,436
Good cops would come forward if they
thought there was encouragement...

1316
01:48:07,510 --> 01:48:09,842
in the department to do so, and if
they thought it would do any good.

1317
01:48:09,912 --> 01:48:11,846
If there's no encouragement,
they're not gonna do it.

1318
01:48:11,914 --> 01:48:15,475
I've done a lot more than most
people to defend and preserve...

1319
01:48:15,551 --> 01:48:18,987
the image of this department
and protect Commissioner Delaney...

1320
01:48:19,055 --> 01:48:22,957
against reckless and irresponsible
assaults from outside agencies.

1321
01:48:24,861 --> 01:48:26,795
That's it, huh?

1322
01:48:26,863 --> 01:48:30,526
I mean, that's what's
really important, isn't it?

1323
01:48:30,600 --> 01:48:32,693
That's what
you want to know...

1324
01:48:32,769 --> 01:48:36,034
what outside agencies
I've been to, right?

1325
01:48:37,573 --> 01:48:39,336
<i>- Hello.
- Hello, prick.</i>

1326
01:48:39,409 --> 01:48:41,536
- Who is this?
- Frank.

1327
01:48:42,412 --> 01:48:45,381
<i>- How are you? Where are you?
- I'm ready to go to the Times.</i>

1328
01:48:46,349 --> 01:48:50,445
It's a goddamn
serious step, Frank.

1329
01:48:50,520 --> 01:48:53,114
I don't know if
the timing is right.

1330
01:48:55,825 --> 01:48:58,623
Look, I want it to get on
the record, that's all...

1331
01:48:58,694 --> 01:49:01,128
in case something
should happen to me.

1332
01:49:04,667 --> 01:49:06,760
I want it on the record.

1333
01:49:09,772 --> 01:49:11,205
I don't know if we
carry enough weight.

1334
01:49:12,875 --> 01:49:14,968
<i>I don't know if the New York Times
will go that far out on a limb...</i>

1335
01:49:15,044 --> 01:49:17,308
on the say-so
of two flunky cops.

1336
01:49:21,617 --> 01:49:24,347
Suppose an inspector
were to come with us?

1337
01:49:25,988 --> 01:49:29,389
You know, I got 20 years
on the force.

1338
01:49:29,459 --> 01:49:33,793
Just bought this place.
I signed a 500-year mortgage on it.

1339
01:49:33,863 --> 01:49:37,094
- Turn that thing off out there!
- Come on. Everybody to bed.

1340
01:49:37,166 --> 01:49:39,191
- Aw, Mom!
- Turn that damn thing down!

1341
01:49:39,268 --> 01:49:41,202
Come on, now.
Go on upstairs.

1342
01:49:41,270 --> 01:49:43,329
You said we could go
to bed late!

1343
01:49:45,007 --> 01:49:47,908
This is against department
regulations, you both know that.

1344
01:49:47,977 --> 01:49:52,277
If they want to throw the book
at me, they can do it.

1345
01:49:52,348 --> 01:49:54,441
If I left the force...

1346
01:49:55,818 --> 01:49:57,911
I don't know
what I could do.

1347
01:50:03,726 --> 01:50:07,662
Okay, I made my little speech.
I'll back you up a hundred percent.

1348
01:50:11,634 --> 01:50:14,865
<i>Times and the News.
I got the money, fellas.</i>

1349
01:50:14,937 --> 01:50:16,871
Here you go, here you go,
here you go.

1350
01:50:16,939 --> 01:50:18,372
<i>Newsweek, please.</i>

1351
01:50:20,776 --> 01:50:22,710
Holy sh... Jeez!

1352
01:50:25,047 --> 01:50:26,674
Aw, Christ!

1353
01:50:26,749 --> 01:50:29,616
You could almost predict
the numbers they're gonna do.

1354
01:50:29,685 --> 01:50:31,949
Delaney's gonna issue
some phony denial.

1355
01:50:32,021 --> 01:50:34,990
Somebody from the mayor's office
will say something noble.

1356
01:50:35,057 --> 01:50:39,687
Delaney'll change his tune. Finally,
the mayor will appoint a commission.

1357
01:50:39,762 --> 01:50:42,959
"Mayor Lindsay announced the
formation of a five-man committee...

1358
01:50:43,032 --> 01:50:45,865
to review the city procedures for
investigating police corruption."

1359
01:50:45,935 --> 01:50:48,995
How come I'm not
in the first paragraph?

1360
01:50:49,071 --> 01:50:50,504
Unbelievable!

1361
01:50:54,777 --> 01:50:59,180
<i>The Times' report smells
of the familiar smear tactics...</i>

1362
01:50:59,248 --> 01:51:01,273
of McCarthyism.

1363
01:51:01,350 --> 01:51:05,810
<i>- I have issued a statement...
- We here at city hall...</i>

1364
01:51:05,888 --> 01:51:08,584
The mayor appointed a special
investigation commission...

1365
01:51:08,658 --> 01:51:10,592
<i>to be headed
by Whitman Knapp.</i>

1366
01:51:10,660 --> 01:51:12,093
Yeah, come.

1367
01:51:17,166 --> 01:51:22,604
It's your reward. It's a transfer
to narcotics, Brooklyn South.

1368
01:51:22,672 --> 01:51:25,835
You're still in clothes. You get
a tin shield, not a gold one.

1369
01:51:30,613 --> 01:51:32,547
I miss you already, Frank.

1370
01:51:37,587 --> 01:51:40,784
Look, Frank...

1371
01:51:43,526 --> 01:51:46,188
it's narcotics.

1372
01:51:46,262 --> 01:51:48,787
You be careful.

1373
01:51:48,864 --> 01:51:52,268
It's very easy to get hurt...

1374
01:51:53,802 --> 01:51:55,235
and to...

1375
01:51:56,839 --> 01:51:58,534
to be set up.

1376
01:52:40,582 --> 01:52:42,607
Get in.

1377
01:52:59,568 --> 01:53:01,661
You're not wired,
are you?

1378
01:53:02,771 --> 01:53:04,636
Okay, you cocksucker.

1379
01:53:06,141 --> 01:53:09,167
You might get by in the Bronx
with that kind of shit...

1380
01:53:09,244 --> 01:53:12,645
but down here,
800 a month is chicken feed.

1381
01:53:14,283 --> 01:53:17,047
Last week,
one dope dealer...

1382
01:53:17,119 --> 01:53:20,179
sent out these guys
making pickups.

1383
01:53:20,255 --> 01:53:22,746
40,000 each.

1384
01:53:22,825 --> 01:53:26,124
We let 'em collect it all,
and then hit 'em.

1385
01:53:26,195 --> 01:53:29,790
120,000 split four ways.

1386
01:53:30,866 --> 01:53:33,266
That's serious money.

1387
01:53:33,335 --> 01:53:36,896
And with that,
you don't fuck around.

1388
01:53:38,674 --> 01:53:41,074
- I got the message.
- Good.

1389
01:53:41,877 --> 01:53:43,310
Now get the fuck out.

1390
01:53:49,985 --> 01:53:51,418
The guy's name is Limbo.

1391
01:53:51,487 --> 01:53:53,819
He just uses this place,
his girlfriend's brother's place.

1392
01:53:53,889 --> 01:53:56,449
He's a pusher... heroin.

1393
01:53:56,525 --> 01:53:58,789
- We'll drive around to the corner.
- Right.

1394
01:53:58,861 --> 01:54:02,524
You keep in sight out front. When
you spot somebody who's dirty...

1395
01:54:02,598 --> 01:54:04,691
take off your glasses
and wipe 'em.

1396
01:54:04,767 --> 01:54:07,292
- Got it?
- Right. Okay.

1397
01:55:15,604 --> 01:55:18,072
We stay around here very long,
we're gonna get spotted.

1398
01:55:18,140 --> 01:55:21,735
Well, Frank, why don't you
go up there and check it out?

1399
01:55:21,810 --> 01:55:25,109
- Why don't you?
- I got the wrong clothes.

1400
01:55:25,181 --> 01:55:27,911
I'll take you shopping.

1401
01:57:12,588 --> 01:57:14,021
Limbo.

1402
01:57:47,056 --> 01:57:48,785
Police. Freeze!

1403
01:57:48,858 --> 01:57:50,883
Police officer.
All right, up against the wall.

1404
01:57:50,960 --> 01:57:55,192
Get your hands up against that wall.
Get up. All right.

1405
01:57:55,264 --> 01:57:58,165
- Palms on the wall and spread 'em.
- Get those hands up!

1406
01:57:58,234 --> 01:58:00,293
- Come on. Spread 'em!
- Get your feet apart.

1407
01:58:01,337 --> 01:58:03,362
- I saw the buy.
- Let's get Limbo. Julio!

1408
01:58:03,439 --> 01:58:05,703
- You all right, baby?
- Yeah, yeah. I got 'em.

1409
01:59:09,772 --> 01:59:11,637
Police officer!

1410
01:59:21,784 --> 01:59:23,752
What the fuck
are you waiting for?

1411
01:59:24,720 --> 01:59:26,881
Go down the fire escape!

1412
01:59:43,039 --> 01:59:46,702
Police! Throw out your guns
and come out with your hands up!

1413
02:00:20,976 --> 02:00:24,139
- Wait. What do you got here?
- It's Mr. and Mrs. Serpico, sir.

1414
02:00:24,213 --> 02:00:26,147
Okay. Go ahead.

1415
02:00:31,420 --> 02:00:34,412
- Where's our son?
- They're bringing him from X-ray.

1416
02:00:34,490 --> 02:00:36,924
- We want to see him.
- Just a few minutes.

1417
02:01:05,054 --> 02:01:06,988
Mr. and Mrs. Serpico...

1418
02:01:07,056 --> 02:01:11,152
the news is better
than we expected.

1419
02:01:11,227 --> 02:01:15,527
Thank God the bullet
was a small caliber.

1420
02:01:15,598 --> 02:01:17,133
It didn't enter the brain...

1421
02:01:18,801 --> 02:01:20,894
or strike the spinal cord.

1422
02:01:22,371 --> 02:01:24,896
He's on the critical list...

1423
02:01:24,974 --> 02:01:28,171
but his condition
seems to be stable.

1424
02:01:29,512 --> 02:01:31,343
Thank you, Doctor.
Thank you.

1425
02:02:05,314 --> 02:02:08,477
Stay out of there.
Didn't they tell you?

1426
02:02:08,551 --> 02:02:10,018
What?

1427
02:02:10,085 --> 02:02:13,452
The word is, don't talk to him.
He's no fuckin' good.

1428
02:02:23,332 --> 02:02:25,926
- How you doing, kid?
- Hello, Sid.

1429
02:02:32,675 --> 02:02:34,609
How are you?

1430
02:02:37,780 --> 02:02:40,214
You wanna read my fan mail?

1431
02:02:40,282 --> 02:02:42,216
Sure.

1432
02:02:42,284 --> 02:02:44,377
You're a big shot now, huh?

1433
02:03:12,615 --> 02:03:16,210
I want you to get those
fucking cops away from my door.

1434
02:03:27,029 --> 02:03:30,590
The Knapp Commission likes you.
They want you to appear.

1435
02:03:30,666 --> 02:03:32,190
Naturally.

1436
02:03:37,039 --> 02:03:38,472
Heinemann and Julio
are cleared.

1437
02:03:38,540 --> 02:03:41,100
The three of you are up for
exceptional merit awards.

1438
02:03:42,645 --> 02:03:44,579
That's very funny.

1439
02:03:49,885 --> 02:03:52,353
That's very funny.

1440
02:03:53,589 --> 02:03:55,022
Francesco, you love me?

1441
02:03:57,326 --> 02:03:59,760
I always had a thing for you, Sid.
You know that.

1442
02:04:04,233 --> 02:04:06,326
Your gold shield's
come through.

1443
02:04:35,064 --> 02:04:36,998
What's this for?

1444
02:04:40,602 --> 02:04:43,298
For being an honest cop?

1445
02:04:45,708 --> 02:04:48,871
Or for being stupid enough
to get shot in the face?

1446
02:04:53,282 --> 02:04:56,251
You tell them
they can shove it.

1447
02:05:01,790 --> 02:05:03,655
I don't want it.

1448
02:05:42,598 --> 02:05:44,031
Oh, well.

1449
02:05:49,238 --> 02:05:51,798
Well, Frank,
the facts are these.

1450
02:05:51,874 --> 02:05:55,503
You'll have to stay on leave
of absence for a few months.

1451
02:05:55,577 --> 02:05:59,445
In all probability, the hearing
in your left ear won't come back.

1452
02:05:59,515 --> 02:06:02,143
Two bullet fragments are still
lodged there in the bony portion.

1453
02:06:02,217 --> 02:06:03,844
One is very close to
the carotid artery...

1454
02:06:03,919 --> 02:06:06,683
<i>and you'll have to be checked
from time to time.</i>

1455
02:06:06,755 --> 02:06:09,155
<i>Your left side will
feel stiff occasionally.</i>

1456
02:06:10,325 --> 02:06:13,488
<i>Once in a great while you may
experience some dizziness.</i>

1457
02:06:13,562 --> 02:06:15,689
<i>But in general,
you'll be okay.</i>

1458
02:06:34,149 --> 02:06:36,447
Through my appearance
here today...

1459
02:06:36,518 --> 02:06:39,544
I hope that police officers in
the future will not experience...

1460
02:06:39,621 --> 02:06:43,216
the same frustration and anxiety
that I was subjected to...

1461
02:06:43,292 --> 02:06:46,591
for the past five years
at the hands of my superiors...

1462
02:06:46,662 --> 02:06:49,597
because of my attempt
to report corruption.

1463
02:06:49,665 --> 02:06:54,432
I was made to feel that I had
burdened them with an unwanted task.

1464
02:06:54,503 --> 02:06:58,064
The problem is that the atmosphere
does not yet exist...

1465
02:06:58,140 --> 02:07:00,074
in which an honest police officer
can act...

1466
02:07:00,142 --> 02:07:04,806
without fear of ridicule
or reprisal from fellow officers.

1467
02:07:04,880 --> 02:07:08,475
Police corruption cannot exist
unless it is at least tolerated...

1468
02:07:08,550 --> 02:07:10,677
at higher levels
in the department.

1469
02:07:10,752 --> 02:07:14,085
Therefore, the most important result
that can come from these hearings...

1470
02:07:14,156 --> 02:07:18,286
is a conviction by police officers
that the department will change.

1471
02:07:19,094 --> 02:07:20,527
In order to ensure this...

1472
02:07:20,596 --> 02:07:23,588
an independent,
permanent investigative body...

1473
02:07:23,665 --> 02:07:27,465
dealing with police corruption,
like this commission, is essential.
